General conditions for
.br
Elektronisk indbetalingskort - debtors
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 5mm
:FED.
1. About Elektronisk indbetalingskort:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
Elektronisk indbetalingskort is a payment slip from a creditor
which the customer receives in &WEBSYSNAVN.. Elektronisk
indbetalingskort contains the same information
as a printed payment slip. The customer can only pay Elektronisk
indbetalingskort by using &WEBSYSNAVN..
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
2. Definitions:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
2.1 Banking Day:SKRSLUT.
.br
Banking days are all days except Saturdays, Sundays, Danish
public holidays, the Friday after Ascension Day, 5 June, 24
December and 31 December.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.2 Payment date:SKRSLUT.
.br
The payment date is the day on which the amount is debited
from the customer's account. Payments are processed on Danish banking
days only.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.3 Payment slip:SKRSLUT.
.br
The term payment slip refers to payment slips used in the
Fælles Indbetalingssystem and the Giro system.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.4 PBS:SKRSLUT.
.br
PBS A/S, CVR no. 20 01 61 75, is the company that enters
into the agreement on Elektronisk indbetalingskort with the
creditor.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.5 Debtor agreement on Elektronisk indbetalingskort:SKRSLUT.
.br
A debtor agreement for Elektronisk indbetalingskort is an
agreement between the customer and &BANKNAVN. enabling the customer to
receive payment slips electronically in &WEBSYSNAVN..
.sp 5mm
