5. Payment execution:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
5.1 The customer's authorisation:SKRSLUT.
.br
To initiate a payment based on an electronic payment slip, the customer
must authorise the payment in his or her &WEBSYSNAVN..
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.2 Payment execution date:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the customer authorises a payment containing the payment data
specified by creditor in an electronic payment slip, the
payment will be executed on the specified payment date with
the specified amount.
.sp 3mm
Before the customer approves the payment, he or she can change the payment
date and the amount disregarding the payment data provided
by creditor.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.3 Liability for the customer's changes in the payment data:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the customer changes the payment data that creditor has specified
in an electronic payment slip or if the customer do not pay, the
matter must be solved between the customer and the creditor. Neither
&BANKNAVN. nor PBS assumes any responsibility in this
connection.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.4 Payment and receipt:SKRSLUT.
.br
An account statement specifying the payment is considered
evidence of the executed payment.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.5 Maximum execution time:SKRSLUT.
.br
The maximum execution time is one banking day from the
payment date the customer has approved; see 5.2.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.6 Cancellation of payment:SKRSLUT.
.br
The customer cannot cancel a payment order after the payment has
been executed.
.sp 3mm
Authorised payments that have not yet been executed may be
cancelled in accordance with the rules that apply to the customer's
&WEBSYSNAVN..
